title: Love Island's Cassie Lansdell is pictured getting cosy with Ed Sheeran
text:
Cassie Lansdell coupled up with Gold Coast 'bad boy' Adam Farrugia on Monday night's episode of Love Island Australia.

But unearthed photos reveal the London-born beauty, 26, has rubbed shoulders with A-list celebrities in the past, including the likes of Ed Sheeran and Liam Payne.

Cassie crossed paths with Ed in 2013, when she shared a photo of herself and the British pop star to Instagram.

Famous friends! Love Island's Cassie Lansdell (left) is pictured getting cosy with Ed Sheeran (centre), Liam Payne and various rappers in newly-surfaced photos. Pictured in 2013

Earlier that year, she posted another photo of herself with Liam Payne when he was still a member of boy band One Direction.

In the snap, Cassie wrapped her arms around Liam's neck as a glamorous female friend leaned on his shoulder.

But her history of meeting famous musicians doesn't stop there, as Cassie has also encountered several famous rappers.

No Payne, no gain! Also in 2013, Cassie (left) met One Direction star Liam Payne (centre)

That's a rap! A bikini-clad Cassie posed for a photo with British rapper Tinie Tempah in 2013, after they bumped into each other at a beach club. Pictured in 2013

A bikini-clad Cassie posed for a photo with British rapper Tinie Tempah in 2013, after they bumped into each other at a beach club.

She has also been pictured with former N-Dubz star Dappy, who looked rather worse for wear as he rested his head on her shoulder.

She met British Olympic driver Tom Daley while partying in Ibiza in 2012 and, later that year, met English singer Conor Maynard during a girls' trip to Las Vegas.

What's going on here? She has also been pictured with former N-Dubz star Dappy (left), who looked rather worse for wear as he rested his head on her shoulder

Fancy seeing you here! Cassie met British Olympic driver Tom Daley (pictured) in Ibiza in 2012

Cassie comes from a mixed Chinese-English background and moved from London to Sydney to work as an executive assistant six years ago.

She's had three Australian boyfriends but has been single for the past eight months after her most recent ex left her heartbroken.

Love Island Australia continues Tuesday at 8:40pm on Channel Nine
